==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pressboard
<hw>Press"board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of highly
sized rag paper or board, sometimes containing a small admixture of wood
pulp; -- so called because used originally, as now, in presses for
pressing and finishing knit underwear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Press cake</ent>⟦br⟧
